description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking for a new role, or considering a change, which would enable you to develop new skills and contribute to the support of patients? We are looking for caring and motivated people to work within our acute stroke unit on 34B. The key responsibilities of this role are: assisting patients making them comfortable and serving beverages and meals. Supporting the ward staff to maintain a high standard of hygiene. Assist with stores ordering, replenishing and maintain stock levels. Ensuring a safe environment, through maintaining a tidy and clean unit.&lt;br /&gt;Part time – 23 hours p/w. On a roster basis including weekends and Bank Holidays. Working long days between 07.00-19.30.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Tanya Matthews&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Ward Sister&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: tanya.matthews@nbt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
